## Tests nested expressions inside transformations
# 1.) get the object in global scope
# 2.) set a variable on the object to the result of the nested expression: {self:var|add 1}
#     the expression is wrapped in an evaluation-delay, so it's not evaluated with the outer expression,
#     but passed raw to the transformation
# 3.) Assert the correctness of both values in the object
set obj.var 1
assign global:result = {global:obj|assign self:val = {1!self:var|add 1}}
eval nop {global:result|get var|assert equals int 1}
eval nop {global:result|get val|assert equals int 2}
exit